en_Answer: The distance between these celestial bodies is constantly changing. In addition, in Russian, or rather Soviet, hockey, emphasis was placed on team play, while in Canadian hockey, a leader stood out who was assisted by other players. Now these differences have become much less noticeable, as there is an active exchange of athletes from different countries. However, purely technical differences remain, for example, in the size of the playing field.

To travel around Russia more cheaply, you can use a car, as the cost of gas is usually less than the cost of train or plane tickets. However, traveling by car will take more time.

To save money when buying train tickets, you can check the schedule of fare changes on the Russian Railways website. It indicates on which days tickets become more expensive or cheaper. Don't forget: Russian Railways has discounts for schoolchildren, students, and pensioners. Children under 5 years old can travel for free, and 7 days before and after their birthday, you can buy a ticket with a 10% discount.

The fastest way to get around is by plane. But you can also save money on air tickets. Many airlines periodically hold sales on air tickets.

To save on accommodation, pay attention not only to hotels but also to small hostels. Additionally, locals often rent out their apartments cheaply during the tourist season and leave themselves. To go on a free or inexpensive tour, look for them on the tripster.ru website.
English: How can you travel around Russia faster and cheaper?
French: Comment pouvez-vous voyager à travers la Russie plus rapidement et à moindre coût ?
German: Wie kann man schneller und günstiger durch Russland reisen?
Hebrew: איך אפשר לטייל ברחבי רוסיה מהר יותר ובזול יותר?

en_Answer: If a person is choking, you should immediately call for an ambulance. While it's on the way, you can try to provide first aid. If the person can't breathe because they're choking on something, you can try applying the Heimlich maneuver. Stand behind the person and wrap your arms around their waist. Clasp one fist with the palm of your other hand and with a sharp thrust, press just above the navel several times. If the person is choking without an apparent reason, don't give them any medication. Open a window to let more air into the room, unbutton the person's collar, and wait for the ambulance to arrive.

en_Answer: The candle burns due to a complex process of oxidation. When the candle wick is ignited, it begins to draw up the molten wax. Under the influence of heat, a chemical oxidation reaction occurs, which releases heat and light - this is the flame of the candle. The heat sustains the process of wax evaporation and ensures the continuity of burning. The light we see is due to the high temperature of the flame.

The color of the Thoracatum catfish is brown, with small spots on the body. This species of catfish has a special intestinal structure that allows them to breathe atmospheric oxygen, so from time to time they rise from the bottom to the surface. en_Answer: The Moon mainly appears yellow or orange at those times when it is rising or setting over the horizon. As a result, the shorter waves of light, such as blue and violet, are scattered, while the longer waves, like orange and red, pass through better.

en_Answer: It was the ancient Egyptians and Sumerians who first divided the day into 24 parts. Their astronomers tracked time by the movement of the stars in the sky. The Egyptians came up with a duodecimal time system. They identified two parts in a day - dark and light time. Each of these parts had 12 hours. However, a similar system was inconvenient because the length of day and night changed at different times of the year. Therefore, the ancient Romans decided to count time in hours. It was much simpler and more convenient: such a division did not depend on the time of year and the length of the day.

en_Answer: The 1990s were a turning point in Russia's history. The collapse of the Soviet Union in 1991 marked the beginning of a new era for the country. Boris Yeltsin became the first president of Russia. The country faced economic difficulties due to the transition to a market economy and the need to establish new production ties. Very high inflation and high unemployment led to a sharp decline in the standard of living. Additionally, from 1994 to 1996, the first Chechen war took place in Russia, claiming many lives. On the other hand, democratic reforms were underway in the country, with the principles of freedom of speech being formed and the institution of elections developing. The 1990s remain one of the most difficult and important periods for Russia in modern history.

German: Was geschah in Russland in den 1990er Jahren?
